use if else

describe('test suite: addToCart', () => {
  
  it('adds an existing product to the cart', () => {
    
  });
  it('adds a new product to the cart', () => {
    addToCart("e43638ce-6aa0-4b85-b27f-e1d07eb678c6");
    expect(cart.length).toEqual(1);
///// in this cart should be initializing with 0 quantity to push to 1 quantity however it initialzes with localstorage so it makes the test flaky
  });
});

flaky Test = test that sometimes passes and sometimes fails

mocks = lets us replace a method with a fake version
spyOn(object, 'method we want to ').and.callFake(fucntion which will overrides the getITem function);

spyOn() records every time a method is used

Unit Tests = testing 1 piece of the code
Integration test = tests many units/pieces of code working together

when testing whole page == 2 things to test:
1. how to page looks
2. how the page behaves

hooks = lets us run some code for each test
beforeEach(() => {

})

1. beforeEach() = runs code before each test
2. afterEach() = runs code after each test
3. beforeAll() = runs code before all tests
4. afterAll() = runs code after all tests



